Introducing methods and research possibilities of family history and sources for researching Estonian family history, learning of researching Estonian family histories.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Aim of the course is to introduce the development of family history research globally and in Estonia, its methods and implenentation of family history in historical research, terminology, problems (historical administrative division, calendar, place and personal names) and sources in Estonia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who passes the course: 1) is aware of possibilities to implement family history in historical research, 2) has acquired knowledge about respective terminology and overview of historical administrative division, calendar, place and personal names, 3) is acquianted with main sources for family history in Estonia and can interpret information in them, 4) is able to compile Estonian peasant genealogies.
